{float:left}</style><div class="ws-header wst-header-structure wst-unknown wst-header ws-header ws-noexport noprint dynlayout-exempt ws-dynlayout-disable"><div class="wst-header-mainblock wst-unknown-mainblock headertemplate"><div class="wst-header-back searchaux wst-unknown-back wst-header-nav-empty"><div class="wst-header-back-arrow">←</div><div class="wst-header-back-link"></div></div><div class="wst-header-central-cell wst-unknown-central-cell"><span class="wst-header-pretitle">Versions of<br /></span><span class="wst-header-title wst-unknown-title"><span class="wst-header-title-text">On the Origin of Species</span><br class="wst-header-title-break" /><span class="contributor-text">by&#160;<span class="fn"><a href="/wiki/Author:Charles_Darwin" class="mw-redirect" title="Author:Charles Darwin">Charles Darwin</a></span></span></span></div><div class="wst-header-forward searchaux wst-unknown-forward wst-header-nav-empty"><div class="wst-header-forward-link"></div><div class="wst-header-forward-arrow">→</div></div></div><div class="wst-header-notes header&#95;notes searchaux wst-unknown-notes"><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r14791120">.mw-parser-output .plainSister{display:block;font-size:93%;line-height:normal;list-style-type:none;list-style-image:none;list-style-position:outside;border:1px solid var(--border-color-interactive--hover,#AAA);float:right;clear:right;margin:0.5ex 0 0.5ex 0.5ex;padding:0;background:var(--background-color-base,#FFFFFF);color:var(--color-base,#202122)}.mw-parser-output .sisicon,.mw-parser-output .dabicon{padding-right:1ex}</style><ul class="plainSister"><li class="sisitem"><span class="sisicon"><span typeof="mw:File/Frameless"><a href="/wiki/Special:SiteMatrix" title="Special:SiteMatrix"><img alt="Sister Projects" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Wikimedia-logo.svg/20px-Wikimedia-logo.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Wikimedia-logo.svg/40px-Wikimedia-logo.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail 2x" data-file-width="1024" data-file-height="1024" /></a></span></span><a href="/wiki/Special:SiteMatrix" title="Special:SiteMatrix">sister projects</a>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/On_the_Origin_of_Species" class="extiw" title="w:On the Origin of Species">Wikipedia article</a>, <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:On_the_Origin_of_Species" class="extiw" title="c:Category:On the Origin of Species">Commons category</a>, <a href="https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/On_the_Origin_of_Species" class="extiw" title="q:On the Origin of Species">quotes</a>, <a href="https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q20124" class="extiw" title="d:Q20124">Wikidata item</a></li></ul><div class="wst-header-content header&#95;notes&#95;content wst-header-notes-content wst-unknown-notes-content">
<p><i>On the Origin of Species</i>, published on 24 November 1859, is a work of scientific literature by <a href="/wiki/Author:Charles_Darwin" class="mw-redirect" title="Author:Charles Darwin">Charles Darwin</a> which is considered to be the foundation of evolutionary biology. Its full title was <i>On the Origin of Species by Means of Natural Selection, or the Preservation of Favoured Races in the Struggle for Life</i>. In the 1872 sixth edition "On" was omitted. This edition is usually known as <i>The Origin of Species</i>. Darwin's book introduced the scientific theory that populations evolve over the course of generations through a process of natural selection. It presented a body of evidence that the diversity of life arose by common descent through a branching pattern of evolution.
</p>
</div></div><div class="ws-noexport" id="ws-data" style="speak:none"><span id="ws-article-id">351535</span><span id="ws-title">On the Origin of Species</span><span id="ws-author">Charles Darwin</span></div></div>
<div class="subNote" style="margin:4px auto 4px auto;"><span id="nofooter">Versions of <b><i>On the Origin of Species</i></b> include:</span></div>
<ul><li><i><a href="/wiki/On_the_Origin_of_Species_(1859)" title="On the Origin of Species (1859)">On the Origin of Species</a></i> (1859), the original edition, published in London by John Murray</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=On_the_Origin_of_Species_(1860)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="On the Origin of Species (1860) (page does not exist)">On the Origin of Species</a></i> (1860), published in London by John Murray</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=On_the_Origin_of_Species_(1861)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="On the Origin of Species (1861) (page does not exist)">On the Origin of Species</a></i> (1861), published in London by John Murray</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=On_the_Origin_of_Species_(1866)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="On the Origin of Species (1866) (page does not exist)">On the Origin of Species</a></i> (1866), published in London by John Murray</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=On_the_Origin_of_Species_(1869)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="On the Origin of Species (1869) (page does not exist)">On the Origin of Species</a></i> (1869), published in London by John Murray</li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Origin_of_Species_(1872)" title="The Origin of Species (1872)">The Origin of Species</a></i> (1872), published in London by John Murray</li></ul>
